canonical:
  title: 禪源社慶讚法會疏
  author: 朴暄
  language: lzh
  text: 道弘佛祖之相傳依舊淸風朗月恩重乾坤而難答如今白髮丹心恭惟我晉陽公刱巨刹以歸誠集作家而辦會奇哉此事萬劫鮮或耳聞我以何緣一朝忽得目覩略支日供仰祝天年伏願金頂戴君久培南山之壽玉峯柱漢永安東海之波
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 禪源社慶讚法會疏
  author: 朴暄
  language: lzh
  text: 道弘佛祖之相傳。依舊淸風朗月。恩重乾坤而難答。如今白髮丹心。恭惟我晉陽公。刱巨刹以歸誠。集作家而辦會。奇哉此事。萬劫鮮或耳聞。我以何緣。一朝忽得目覩。略支日供。仰祝天年。伏願金頂戴君。久培南山之壽。玉峯柱漢。永安東海之波。
korean:
  title: 선원사에서 경찬법회를 베푸는 글
  author: 박훤
  language: kor
  text: 큰 도는 불조(佛祖)로부터 전해오므로 맑은 바람과 밝은 달이 옛날 그대로이고, 무거운 은혜는 건곤(乾坤)과 같아 보답하기 어렵기에 지금 수염이 희게 되었어도 마음은 그대로이옵니다. 생각하건대, 우리 진양공(晉陽公)은 거찰(巨刹)을 세워 정성을 기울이고, 작가(作家)를 모아 법회를 마련하오니, 희귀한 이런 일은 만겁(萬劫)을 통해 듣기도 어렵거늘, 나는 무슨 인연으로 일조(一朝)에 직접 보게 되었습니까. 이에 약간의 공양을 베풀고 우러러 천년(天年)을 비옵니다. 원하건대, 금 이마[金頂]로 임금을 받들어 남산(南山) 같은 오랜 수명을 북돋아 주고, 옥 봉우리로 나라를 지켜 동해(東海)의 물결이 길이 안정하게 하옵소서.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1140_010_0230&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Eulogy for the Dharma Assembly Celebration at Seonwon Temple
  author: Park Hwon
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The great Way transmitted from the Buddhas and Patriarchs remains—clear wind and bright moon as in ancient days. Yet the weight of their compassion spans heaven and earth, and how can we repay it? Though my hair has turned white with age, my heart stays true.

    I contemplate our Lord of Jinyang, who erected this great temple as an offering of devotion, and gathered the worthy to hold this sacred assembly. How rare is such a feat! In ten thousand kalpas, few have heard its like. What fortunate karma brought me to witness it this very day with these eyes?

    I present these humble offerings and lift my prayers for your longevity. May the golden crown upon your brow endure with the eternal life of South Mountain, and may the jade peak of your virtue guard the realm, keeping the Eastern Sea forever calm and blessed.
  footnotes:
    - 'Jinyang (晉陽公): A title of honor referring to an eminent patron or ruler'
    - 'South Mountain (南山): A classical allusion to longevity and permanence'
    - 'Eastern Sea: A symbol of national stability and prosperity in East Asian tradition'
